"recipients" may be individuals or organizations.

  To "modify" a work means to copy from or adapt all or part of the work
in a fashion requiring copyright permission, other than the making of an
exact copy. The resulting work is called a "modified version" of the
earlier work, or a work "based on" the earlier work.

  A "covered work" means either the unmodified Program or a work based
on the Program.

  "Propagate" a work means to do anything with it that, without
permission, would make you directly or secondarily liable for
infringement under applicable copyright law, except executing on a user
computer, virtual machine, or similar. Conveying a work means anything
that propagates or modifies it.

  An "organizational action" means actions that affect an organization
or are taken on behalf of an organization, and do not merely have
individual implications.

  "Convey" means to engage in any of the above with or without user
action, during the duration of the copyright.

  You may make, run and propagate covered works that you do not
convey, without conditions so long as your license otherwise remains
in force. You may convey a covered work to others only for the purpose
